## Headless Scenario Presets (your domain)

These live in `tools/screenshot_scenarios.py` and `tools/observe_sync.py`:

| Scenario | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `default` | Standard gameplay |
| `intent_bounty` | Bounty pursuit QA |
| `hero_stuck_repro` | Stuck hero recovery |

When you need a new behavior verified automatically, spec a new scenario preset and ask Agent 12 to wire it into the tools.

## Your Typical Sprint Role

- **Early sprint (R1)**: Spec out any new content/scenario requirements
- **Mid sprint**: Review implementation against your content spec
- **End sprint**: Verify scenario presets pass headless QA; update content backlog

## Current Content Backlog (known from sprint history)

- More enemy types (beyond goblin/wolf/skeleton/skeleton_archer/spider/bandit)
- More building types with meaningful strategic choices
- World events: raids, festivals, disasters (not yet implemented)
- Multiple scenario goals (not just "survive waves") for Early Access replayability
- Journey behavior polish (v1.3 — in progress)

## Who to Coordinate With

- **Agent 02 (GameDirector)**: get approval on new content before speccing it
- **Agent 05 (Gameplay)**: tuning/balance for new scenarios
- **Agent 06 (AI Behavior)**: hero behavior should support your scenarios
- **Agent 11 (QA)**: your scenario specs become headless test scenarios
